	<li>Productivity application support</li>
	<li>Convergence</li>
	<li>Instant messaging</li>
</ul>
<h3>Topic Area: Infrastructure</h3>
<p>A strategic imperative is establishing and maintaining a robust technical infrastructure to support both academic and administrative needs while accommodating rapid change. The elements of this infrastructure range from network design, hardware, and operating systems to Web services, network system management, directory and authentication services, imaging and multimedia systems, to grids and on-demand services. An industrial-strength infrastructure is required to support the teaching, learning, research, and administrative needs of the e-institution. </p>
<p>Key topics include:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Web services</li>
	<li>Identity management</li>
	<li>Directory services</li>
