	<li>Service level agreements</li>
	<li>File and print services</li>
	<li>Network security</li>
</ul>
<h3>Topic Area: Research Computing and Advanced Networking</h3>
<p>Nearly every academic discipline uses IT to support research and scholarship. Nowhere is the move to distributed IT and support more evident than in research computing or scholarly information management. IT is particularly facilitating interinstitutional collaboration via grid computing, shared networked resources, and collaborative applications. While IT services are not intended to be a research area per se, they provide the institutional context for successful contemporary research activities. </p>
<p>Key topics include:</p>
<ul>
	<li>Collaborative applications</li>
	<li>Research applications</li>
	<li>Research computing</li>
	<li>Advanced networking</li>
