</ul>
<h3>Topic Area: Security Policy and Practices</h3>
<p>Emerging legal, ethical, and appropriate information use issues have placed a higher priority on the development of policies and response strategies at our institutions, including the need to respond to legislation and regulation. Meanwhile, technical tools have given us greater capacity to control and monitor desktops users' technology use. How can policy, mindful of law and ethics, guide us to the proper balance between the easy access to information that is a hallmark of higher education and responsible management of our information infrastructure? How have other organizations created processes to write policies and procedures? </p>
<p>Key topics include:</p>
<ul>
