<h3>Topic Area: Data Privacy</h3>
<p>Higher education has been tackling traditional issues such as intellectual property rights, personal and institutional privacy, and academic integrity for many years. Emerging legal, ethical, and appropriate information use issues have placed a higher priority on the development of policies and response strategies at our institutions, including the need to respond to legislation such as the USA PATRIOT Act, Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act, HIPAA, FERPA, and the Digital Millennium Copyright Act. </p>
